Or let’s work out an agreeable BEST OFFER price. Always willing to work with buyers. The PRS Custom 24 a perennial favorite with guitar players. The Custom 24 is the original PRS; the guitar Paul Reed Smith company was founded on, the guitar Paul Reed Smith took to his first trade show in 1985, and the first guitar produced in the PRS factory. To celebrate its 25th Anniversary, PRS offered the PRS Custom 24 guitar with special features such as shadow bird inlays, anniversary headstock eagle, bound rosewood fretboard, 57/08 pickups and a gorgeous carved flamed maple “10” top. Standard features of this PRS guitar include a mahogany back and sides, natural maple body binding, a 25″ scale length, a standard PRS neck profile, nickel hardware, Phase II low-mass locking tuners and the patented PRS tremolo bridge. The 25th Anniversary PRS Custom 24 guitar is loaded with 1957/2008 pickups that allow players to achieve both vintage and modern sounds. PRS obtained the rights to the original pickup wire used in the most revered pickups in the 50’s in 2008, and 1957 was the year the humbucker was first commercially available, giving rise to the 1957/2008 name. A 5-way rotary switch expands the tonal possibilities with a variety of pickup coil combinations. Complete with original white 25th anniversary Tolex hardshell case and white strap.
